  The Startup-sequence
  ====================

  Every time your machine boots it automatically executes the 
  Startup-sequence script located in the "S" drawer. Its purpose is to 
  initialize drivers, user preference settings, and create assigns, 
  among other common startup duties.
  
  The following is a breakdown of an ordinary AmigaOS 3.2 
  Startup-sequence script along with comments describing what each 
  section does. Don't be alarmed if it does not exactly match yours.
  This example is only meant to provide you with a general overview of 
  the process. 

---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
  Version exec.library version 47 >NIL:
  If Warn
    LoadModule L:System-Startup ROMUPDATE
    Else
      Version strap version 47 >NIL:
      If Warn
        LoadModule DOWNGRADE L:Ram-Handler L:Shell-Seg L:System-Startup Libs:dos.library Libs:gadtools.library Libs:graphics.library >NIL:
      EndIf
  EndIf
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Checks if the Kickstart ROM is an updated 3.2 one. If not, it 
  runs a soft-loading mechanism involving an automatic reboot. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  SetPatch >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Applies several patches and fixes to many OS components. Since we 
  don't like to have the list shown, it is redirected to NIL:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  FailAt 31
  CPU CHECKINSTALL

  SET temp1 $RC

  If VAL $temp1 EQ 30
    ECHO ""
    ASK "Press the RETURN key to resume booting into a restricted system."
    Execute S:Startup-failsafe
    QUIT
  EndIf

  If VAL $temp1 EQ 5
    ECHO ""
    ASK "Press the RETURN key to resume booting."
  EndIf

  UNSET temp1
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  If no CPU support libraries are detected for 68040/60 processors 
  that require them, an optional restricted Startup-failsafe script is 
  offered to be executed so that the user may perform some maintenance 
  and troubleshooting operations with relative safety.
  
  If on the other hand, no CPU support libraries are detected for 
  68030 processors, only a warning is displayed and the user may 
  resume booting by pressing the return key.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  FailAt 10
  Version >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Sets the script error's level of tolerance to its default value. 
  Initializes Kickstart and Workbench variables.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Assign >nil: EXISTS DF0:
  If not warn
    AddBuffers DF0: 15 >NIL:
  EndIf
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Sets the amount of memory buffers for the first floppy drive only if 
  there is one to begin with. This makes the floppy drive a little bit 
  faster.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  If EXISTS ENVARC:
     MakeLink RAM:ENV to ENVARC: FORCE
  Else
     MakeDir RAM:ENV
  Endif
  MakeDir RAM:T RAM:Clipboards
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Creates several temporal directories. 
  It also performs a "copy on demand" from ENVARC: to ENV:
  Its purpose is to integrate env-handling features into
  RAM, and avoid unnecessary copying of files into RAM:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Resident C:Assign PURE
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Loads the Assign command into memory to speed up its execution.
   
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Assign ENV: RAM:ENV
  Assign T: RAM:T
  Assign CLIPS: RAM:Clipboards
  Assign REXX: S:

  FailAt 21
  Assign PRINTERS: DEVS:Printers
  Assign KEYMAPS: DEVS:Keymaps
  Assign LOCALE: SYS:Locale
  Assign LIBS: SYS:Classes ADD
  Assign HELP: LOCALE:Help DEFER
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Generates multiple Assigns required for proper OS usage.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  BindDrivers
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Loads some specific third party drivers that reside in the 
  "Expansion" drawer.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Mount DEVS:DOSDrivers/~(#?.info)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Looks for all the mount files in Devs:DOSDrivers and attempts to 
  mount them all.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  C:LoadMonDrvs >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Takes care of loading display drivers. If the CyberGraphX RTG system 
  is found, countermeasures to prevent some of its bugs are launched.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  FailAt 10
  SetEnv Language "english"
  SetEnv Workbench $Workbench
  SetEnv Kickstart $Kickstart
  UnSet Workbench
  UnSet Kickstart
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Sets several environment variables.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  AddDataTypes REFRESH QUIET
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Looks for Data Types in Devs:DataTypes and loads them.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  IPrefs
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Loads and sets the user-defined preferences, which were previously 
  configured by the Preference editors (Located in the Prefs drawer).

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  ConClip
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Starts the Console and Shell clipboard functionality.
  
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  If EXISTS SYS:System/RexxMast
    SYS:System/RexxMast >NIL:
  EndIF
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Activates the Amiga Rexx interpreter.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Path C: SYS:Utilities SYS:Rexxc SYS:System S: SYS:Prefs SYS:Tools SYS:Tools/Commodities
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Defines the access path for programs so that they can be directly 
  run from the CLI/Shell without having to specify their exact 
  location.
  
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  MakeLink SOFT RAM:Disk.info TO ENVARC:Sys/def_RAM.info SOFT
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Any changes done to RAM:Disk.info are automatically saved to disk.
  
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  IF EXISTS S:User-Startup
    Execute S:User-Startup
  EndIF
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  If a script file in S: named User-startup is found, it gets 
  executed.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  LoadWB
  EndCLI >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Loads Workbench and closes the current CLI/Shell interface.
  